last_task_title: Fix Memory Router receiving string instead of config object (8 failures)
last_task_description:
Fix AttributeError: str object has no attribute user_id_mappings in test_memory_proxy.py and test_memory_routing.py tests.

ROOT CAUSE:
- Tests passing string config path to MemoryRouter()
- MemoryRouter expects LiteLLMProxyConfig object, not string
- Error occurs when MemoryRouter tries to access config.user_id_mappings

AFFECTED TESTS (8 failures):
- test_memory_routing.py::test_model_detection
- test_memory_routing.py::test_header_injection  
- test_memory_proxy.py::TestMemoryRouterInit (all 4 tests)
- test_memory_proxy.py::TestPerformance::test_router_performance_many_patterns
- test_memory_proxy.py::TestEdgeCases (2 tests)

SOLUTION:
Update all MemoryRouter() instantiations to load config first:
  from proxy.schema import load_config_with_env_resolution
  config = load_config_with_env_resolution(config_file)
  memory_router = MemoryRouter(config)

FILES TO FIX:
- tests/test_memory_routing.py (search for MemoryRouter() calls)
- tests/test_memory_proxy.py (search for MemoryRouter() calls)

VALIDATION:
Run: poetry run pytest tests/test_memory_routing.py tests/test_memory_proxy.py::TestMemoryRouterInit -v
Verify all 8 tests PASS, no AttributeError str object errors
